                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#2ra">Fols. 2ra</locus>-b, 4vb: Mälkǝʿ-hymn in praise of the Trinity.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 2ra, ls.1-3: ሰላም፡ ለህላዌክሙ፡ ዘኢይመውዕ፡ ለዊተ፡ ለረከበ፡ ስሙ፡ ኅቡዕ፡ ድኅረ፡ ወጠንኩ፡ ተምኔተ፡…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Crudely written, some parts of the text poorly legible.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#5r">Fol. 5r</locus>(in the upper margin): Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 5r: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘአቶ፡ ተንሥአ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ዘተሣየጣ፡ በወርቁ፡ ዘወሀባ፡ ለመቅደሰ፡ ፈቃዳ፡ ወለቄሰ፡ ገበዝሂ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ኅቡረ፡ ይምሐሮሙ፡ {ዘሠረቃ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን።}</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 5r: This is a book of ʾato Tänśǝʾa Krǝstos, who bought it with his own money, who donated it to the sanctuary of Fäqada and to qesä gäbäz Ṗeṭros. May (God) be merciful to them both. He who steals it or erases (its text) shall be excommunicated.</q>
                           Written partly in red, partly in black ink.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#110ra">Fols. 110ra-111</locus>vb: Prayer to the Virgin Mary for protection, unidentified, incomplete (?).<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 110ra, ls.11-14: ዘኢገብሮ፡ እደ፡ ሰብእ፡ ዘሂ፡ አስተዮ፡ ለጽሙዕ፡ በእንተ፡ ስምኪ፡ &lt;...&gt;አስተዮ፡ ጽዋዓ፡ ሕይወት፡ እምፈለገ፡ ማየ፡ ሕይወት፡...</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Crudely written, probably by the same hand as Additio 1.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#112ra">Fols. 112ra-114</locus>rb: Prayer to the Virgin Mary for protection, unidentified, incomplete (?).<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Crudely written. Possibly a continuation or part of Additio 3, executed in the same hand as Additiones 1 and 3.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Fol. 1v: Crude notes in pencil mentioning the region of ʿƎndärta and of a person named Gäbrä Sǝllase. Traces of text visible (most probably traces of ink from the facing page).&#xD;
- Fol. 96vb: Crude hardly readable note, partly washed out.</item>
                     </list>
